<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-45] Referring to a class name in Groovy to another Groovy class thats not yet been turned into bytecode causes a compile error</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-45</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If you do uncomment the &apos;todo&apos; text in groovy.gdo.Person test so that the Person is used as an expression, then do&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;maven clean test&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the test will fail.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is due to the Person class not being found at the time the PersonTest is being compiled.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We need to have an interim step which once we&apos;ve created the AST will spot class names as variables and expand them as ClassExpressions using the AST as well as the classpath&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12812138">GROOVY-45</key>
            <summary>Referring to a class name in Groovy to another Groovy class thats not yet been turned into bytecode causes a compile error</summary>
